anualResolver` to manage endpoints and load balance\n4. Request is intercepted by `unaryClientInterceptor` (or `streamClientInterceptor` for Watch/Lease)\n5. On error, `isSafeRetry()` determines if retry is appropriate based on operation type\n6. `waitRetryBackoff()` applies exponential backoff with jitter before retry\n7. For Watch and Lease streams, `streamClientInterceptor` manages stream-specific retry with buffering\n8. Context deadline is respected throughout, enforcing request timeout from the caller's `context.WithTimeout()`\n9. Keepalive pings maintain connection health, with response timeout enforced by `DialKeepAliveTimeout`\n\nThis architecture ensures reliable client-side operation with transparent retry and timeout enforcement across all operation types (KV, Watch, Lease) while maintaining consistency guarantees and avoiding duplicate writes."
